metadata.name: Belphegor (those who spread sorrow and tears )
metadata.description:
Name: Belphegor
Form: Demon
Hierarchy: Qlipoth
Step: -6
Thagirion: those who spread sorrow and tears 
Size: 6000 x 12000 px, 300 DPI
Creator: Polygonist
Co-Creator: Machine

Belphegor is the form of the name of the Moabite deity Baal Peor (בעל פעור "Lord of Peor") or also Baal Pegor, which has been handed down in the Septuagint (βεελφεγωρ LXX) and then in the Vulgate (Beelphegor VUL). As a demon, Belphegor found his way into Christian mythology and from there into Renaissance literature and modern popular culture.
